	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I camped the Glacier Bear for just over 1 hour when he appeared. He spawns at the entrance to the house with the skeletons in it. He is as big as a mammoth and cons blue to me. I am level 34 Barabarian Shaman. I cast my toughest spell on him(winters roar) and he resisted it. Seeing that he resisted my spell I sat back and let my pet kill him while I healed my pet and hit the bear every once in a while to distract and inflict damage. I greater healed my pet with greater healing 3 times and he killed the bear. And the bear dropped the pelt only. One footnote is that my pet conned blue to me which puts him in the 25-27 range. So if you pull a green pet, kill him and summon a new one.<BR>
My recommendation to someone wanting this is to try and summon a tough pet and sit back and heal your pet. You will surely die if you waste all your mana on him and he kills your pet. He is very tough! Good luck and don't believe all the others who say this is a easy bear...he is not easy.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
